AUDITING:
=========
	- when we perform operations on a table those operational information will store 
in an other table is known as "Auditing Table".

EX:
SQL> CREATE TABLE TEST(STID NUMBER(4),SNAME VARCHAR2(10),SFEE NUMBER(8,2));
SQL> CREATE TABLE TEST_AUDIT(STID NUMBER(4),AUDIT_INFR VARCHAR2(100));

Auditing on INSERT command:
==========================
SQL> CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER TRAUDIT1
    BEFORE INSERT ON TEST
    FOR EACH ROW
    BEGIN
    INSERT INTO TEST_AUDIT VALUES(:NEW.STID,'You inserted a new row into a table on:'||TO_CHAR(SYSDATE,'DD-MON-YYYY HH:MI:SS PM'));
    END;
    /
TESTING:
=========
SQL> INSERT INTO TEST VALUES(1,'ALLEN',23000);
SQL> SELECT * FROM TEST;
SQL> SELECT * FROM TEST_AUDIT;
